README
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

This patchset is for the latest linux kernel provided by grml.org.
It is usually based on genpatches, ubuntu-2.6.git, debian patches and
work by the Grml team.

Patchset Numbering Scheme
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

FIXES
1000-1400       linux-stable
1400-1500       linux-stable queue
1500-1700       security
1700-1800       architecture-related
1800-1900       mm/scheduling/misc
1900-2000       filesystems
2000-2100       networking core
2100-2200       storage core
2200-2300       power management (ACPI, APM)
2300-2400       bus (USB, IEEE1394, PCI, PCMCIA, ...)
2400-2500       network drivers
2500-2600       storage drivers
2600-2700       input
2700-2900       media (graphics, sound, tv)
2900-3000       other
3000-4000       reserved

FEATURES
4000-4100       network
4100-4200       storage
4200-4300       graphics
4300-4400       filesystem
4400-4500       other

GRML
5000-5100       Grml specific, arch independent
5100-5200       Grml specific, arch dependent

Individual Patch Descriptions:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Patch:  1000_3.0.X
From:   http://kernel.org/
Desc:   stable series patch

Patch:  4200_vesa_fallback_on_fail.patch
From:   https://svn.pardus.org.tr/pardus/playground/ozan/kernel/kernel-next/files/pardus/vesa_fallback_on_fail.patch
Desc:   Fall back to vesa-mode instead of hitting undefined video mode number

Patch:  4300_aufs_for_3.1.patch
From:   based on http://git.c3sl.ufpr.br/pub/scm/aufs/aufs2-standalone.git
Desc:   Support for aufs filesystem (version 2)

Patch:  5000_grml_logo.patch
From:   http://git.grml.org/?p=grml-kernel.git
Desc:   Grml-logo in framebuffer

Patch:  {x86,amd64}/5100_grml-version.patch
From:   http://git.grml.org/?p=grml-kernel.git
Desc:   adjust kernel version for the Grml-system (add -grml[64])

